      "message": "Good question; I had actually included this here without thinking about it much, since it was in the diagram.\n\nBut now that I think about it... I\u0027m not sure it\u0027s necessary.\n\n - All cleanup can be done in Update; GobWatchMap entities could also be removed.\n - Regardless of the last updated time, we can just update all entities that need to be updated. UpdatedTime doesn\u0027t need to be used during update.\n\nAnd if there\u0027s no UpdatedTime, then actually... I believe we don\u0027t need to ever put any GobWatchMap entities in datastore; I believe that the only purpose that the GobWatchMap level of the hierarchy serves is so that we can do ancestor queries based on a host/repo key. Does that sound right?",
